snippet.textDisplay:
Thanks for watching this video. I'm glad you're here. If you feel like this earns your subscription please click here: http://bit.ly/Subscribe2SED


How this happened: I messaged Tory "If you ever find yourself with an open lunch I'll buy. No cameras, just rocket geek chat."
A few months later he changed a flight one day so we could grab lunch, but he also carved out a couple of hours before lunch to give me a personal tour.
He's as cool off camera as he is on camera. He allowed me to ask any technical question I had, and I never even got close to the limits of his understanding of rockets. His technical prowess is something I aspire to. We made a video on the second channel where I interview him about more specific things about rockets, as well as how he feels about competitors.
2nd Channel Interview with Tory about rocket engines, competitors, and business philosophy: https://youtu.be/DQaPOIQLEUo

snippet.textDisplay: I really enjoyed watching this video. It was awesome to see how the rockets are made, etc.  My question is, has anyone seen that NASA SPACE FLIGHT: Bocachica YT video of the construction of a rocket by SpaceX/Elon Musk. And do you think that trying to  build a rocket that way,  will actually fly???  I'm not a  rocket scientist or an engineer, but I think I know enough, to say that what they're attempt to do just looks ridiculous. To me it has no structural integrity or stability.  It seriously reminded me of a grain silo.  I would like to hear your thoughts and answers.  Thank you, Tory  I love watching your videos.

snippet.textDisplay: I would not normally watch an hour video....but so glad I did. Mr. Buno is intelligent, engaged, passionate, genuine and a dozen other positive qualities I'm sure. It's like he is still a little kid reaching for the stars....literally. VERY impressed with him, and the rockets were okay too. The fact that the human eye is MORE accurate than automation when rolling the aluminum is incredible. I can't imagine the cost or stress involved should the tolerance be off and have to start over. Thanks for another great video....
